            "title": "Backticks ` `",
            "content": "Template Literals use backticks (` `) instead of quotes (' ' or \" \").\n\nThey have two superpowers:\n1. Multi-line strings\n2. String Interpolation"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l4_2",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Interpolation ✨",
            "content": "You can put variables directly inside the string using `${name}`!",
            "codeSnippet": "let name = 'Alice';\nconsole.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
